VALUES ('c0b7ef48-b139-4ad8-b990-08e5408acc6a', 'Which choice completes the text with the most logical transition?', 'Eleanor distrusted the new neighbor''s friendliness, certain that his constant offers to help concealed some hidden motive. Months passed, and he asked for nothing in return, quietly shoveling her walk and fetching her mail without comment. ______, she began to suspect that his kindness was exactly what it appeared to be.', NULL, '[{"id":"A","text":"Eventually,","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct: it marks the gradual passage of time leading to her changed conclusion."},{"id":"B","text":"Nevertheless,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Wrong: her new suspicion follows naturally from his behavior, not in spite of it."},{"id":"C","text":"By comparison,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Wrong: nothing is being compared; the sentence reports an outcome over time."},{"id":"D","text":"In short,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Wrong: the sentence introduces a developed change, not a summary of preceding points."}]'::jsonb, 'A', 'Step 1 — Track the timeline
The passage notes that {{yellow:Months passed, and he asked for nothing in return}}, signaling a process unfolding over time.
Step 2 — Choose the relationship
